"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-30-fencer-reveals-won-paris-olympics-seven-months-pregnant-21329788\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Nada Hafez was seven months pregnant when she beat Elizabeth Tartakovsky 15-13 at the ParisOlympics, the Egyptian fencer has revealed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nada_Hafez\", \"score\": 0.9999996836818855, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nada Hafez\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nada_Hafez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nada_Hafez\"}, {\"begin\": 51, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9410116281849211, \"rank\": 0.061593804045680135, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 105, \"end\": 113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egyptians\", \"score\": 0.9936305636354971, \"rank\": 0.006263578260554619, \"text\": \"Egyptian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egyptians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egyptians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hafez eliminated her Team USA opponent in the first round of the women's individual sabre before suffering defeat to South Korean star Jeon Hayoung.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 136, \"end\": 141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\", \"score\": 0.9462492431318434, \"rank\": 0.05680401570554209, \"text\": \"Hafez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\"}, {\"begin\": 157, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.7006199040608744, \"rank\": 0.42380642691299536, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 259, \"end\": 270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MV_Korean_Star_(1984)\", \"score\": 0.999939898263772, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Korean star\", \"types\": [\"Q11446\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MV_Korean_Star_(1984)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MV_Korean_Star_(1984)\"}, {\"begin\": 276, \"end\": 283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oh_Ha-young\", \"score\": 0.9999999888655112, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hayoung\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oh_Ha-young\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oh_Ha-young\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 26-year-old has now taken toInstagramto confirm that she was in fact heavily pregnant when she recorded the Olympic win over Tartakovsky.\", \"from\": 286, \"to\": 427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'7 MONTHS PREGNANT OLYMPIAN!'\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 458, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hafez posted.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\", \"score\": 0.9462492431318434, \"rank\": 0.05680401570554209, \"text\": \"Hafez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'What appears to you as two players on the podium, they were actually three!\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 549, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It was me, my competitor, & my yet-to-come to our world, little baby!\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My baby & I had our fair share of challenges, be it both physical & emotional.\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'The rollercoaster of pregnancy is tough on its own, but having to fight to keep the balance of life & sports was nothing short of strenuous, however worth it.\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 861, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am writing this post to say that pride fills my being for securing my place in the round of 16!\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am lucky to have shared the trust of my husband @ibrahimihab11 and that of my family to be able to come this far.\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 1079, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'This specific Olympics was different; Three times Olympian but this time carrying a little Olympian one!'\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999994628118736, \"rank\": 5.371884497211099e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hafez has competed in sabre at the last three Olympic Games in a row - Rio 2016, Tokyo 2020 and now Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1189, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\", \"score\": 0.9462492431318434, \"rank\": 0.05680401570554209, \"text\": \"Hafez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hafez\"}, {\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8983210975606232, \"rank\": 0.11318770328761853, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1289, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999949257017, \"rank\": 5.074225450504353e